metadata.name: Treasured Rug #178
metadata.description:
A form of concrete poetry depicting a rug.
Typography created by multiple lines of typewriter text.
Features one of five possible character sets.
One of ten possible palettes for text color
90% chance of black paper, or 10% chance of white
10% chance of rare "Wild" character shift, otherwise 45% of either "Loose" or "Tight"
15% chance each of either rare "Narrow" or "Wide" rug otherwise "Standard"
3 styles of paper grain
Differing line gaps
Differing types of skew effect
Differing types of blend effect when characters overlay.

Press S to save in High Resolution

Uses p5.js and scribble.js
@p1x3lboy August 2022

metadata.description:

metadata.name: UFO #76
metadata.description:
Friend or Foe? ... Orb, Hourglass or Donut? .. who knows? 
These 300 reflective UFOs have been discovered beyond the Kuiper Belt.
All are truly unique. with differing patterns, palettes, stroke colors, sizes and levels of brightness.
Each UFO has four different colored lights shining on it to produce the metallic effect.

Keys for Interaction are as follows:
"R" - To change the rotation of your UFO - morphing it into a different shape
"4" - To produce in a higher resolution
"2" - To produce in a high resolution
"1" - To produce in a standard resolution
"S" - To save a JPG image of your UFO in its current state
"P" - To produce a PNG image of your UFO in its current state

Created by P1xelboy January 2023 using p5.js and WEBGL

metadata.name: Subdivision Squares #13
metadata.description:
This is an original Op Art piece that incorporates an algorithm for drawing alternating black and white concentric squares inside a space defined by of another algorithm that divides the picture space in half (alternatively vertically or horizontally) on consecutive iterations. A coin-toss algorithm decides which half to fill with concentric squares and the other half is further divided in half again. The subdivision process iterates until the half space is too small to draw squares in.

Check out Dr. Bill Generative Art OG website @ drbillkolomyjec.com

metadata.name: Calligraphy #116
metadata.description:
Calligraphy is about formulating letters, not language. 

One of my first exercises as a design student (c. 1967) was learning to letter. Using a nib holding pen and India ink we sat for 5 weeks in class like monks constructing letters in the style of a font called 15th Century Chancery Italic Script. Our final grade was based on how well we hand lettered a paragraph. It was a grueling process that's why I remember it; quite the way to develop an appreciation for the letterforms and type faces. 

This algorithmic artwork is modern cuneiform. It is based on a theory I've developed called "Language of Vision" which in itself is an approach for creating a "plastic" image. The space-frame or background square consists of a subtle paper texture and defines the tablet. A resizable tile (spatial force) forms the boundary for a "stroke." The stroke within the tile element is created by joining two bezier curves. 

An algorithm called "fractions of the whole" is a "form of spatial organization" which divides the picture frame into randomly sized intervals along each axes that form the variable sized tile areas. The stroke is programmed to fit each area. This theory lends itself very nicely to algorithmic art and provides a general framework for generative art.

There is meaning in every image but that meaning comes from your experience and imagination.

Check out Dr. Bill Generative Art OG website @ drbillkolomyjec.com

metadata.name: Syzers #288
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

···· On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ····

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template. 
"FXHASH PFP Token Generator" https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

for best resolution "open live" then use the "download image" button on the lower right corner ;)
